{{for|the [[South American]] Sun god|Adaheli}}
'''ADAHELI''', ADvanced Astronomy for HELIophysics, is an [[Italy|Italian]] [[sun|solar]] [[satellite]] project for the investigation of solar activity and dynamics.<ref name=torverg>{{cite web |title=ADAHELI Mission |publisher=Physics Department of Tor Vergata University |url=https://www.fisica.uniroma2.it/~solare/english/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=1:adaheli-mission&catid=11:projects&Itemid=3|access-date=22 April 2016}}</ref> It is designed to investigate the fast dynamics of the solar [[photosphere]] and [[chromosphere]] performing visible and NIR broad-band and monochromatic observations.<ref>{{cite web |title=The Fabry-Perot interferometer prototype for the ADAHELI solar small mission |publisher=Spie-Int Soc Optical Engineering |url=https://www.researchgate.net/publication/228091605_The_Fabry-Perot_interferometer_prototype_for_the_ADAHELI_solar_small_mission |access-date=22 April 2016}}</ref>
On board instruments will be a millimeter band [[radiometer]] and a VIS-NIR (visible and near infrared spectrum) high resolution telescope.<ref name=torverg />
Other major objectives of [[NASA]], [[ESA]], and the international [[Living with a Star]] program, such as the [[Solar Dynamics Observatory]], [[PICARD]], [[Solar Orbiter]], and the [[Parker Solar Probe]] missions, are complemented without overlap by the ADAHELI instrument suite.<ref>{{cite web |title=The ADAHELI Solar Mission |publisher=SAO/NASA ADS Astronomy Abstract Service |bibcode=2008ESPM...12..6.6B |access-date=22 April 2016}}</ref>
