{{Infobox glacier | name = Bowers Piedmont Glacier | photo = | photo_caption = | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Bowers Piedmont Glacier in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = piedmont glacier | location = [[Victoria Land]], [[Antarctica]] | coords = {{coord|77|43|S|164|14|E|type:glacier_source:gnis_region:AQ|display=inline,title}}<ref> {{cite gnis|1550|name=Blue Glacier|accessdate=2008-10-07|type=antarid}} </ref> | area = | length = | thickness = | terminus = | status = }} '''Bowers Piedmont Glacier''' is a [[piedmont glacier]] on the coast of [[Victoria Land]], covering about {{convert|40|sqmi}} and lying just south of [[New Harbour (Antarctica)|New Harbour]]. It merges at its south side with [[Blue Glacier (Antarctica)|Blue Glacier]].
